## discard all the rows that are part of time stretches where entire microcosms has (seemingly) gone extinct
#%>%dplyr::filter(is_after_first_zero_day==FALSE)

complete_aggr<-aggr_ts%>%group_by(composition,nutrients,temperature,sample_ID)%>%summarise(
  mean_biom=mean(tot_biomass),
  CV=sd(tot_biomass)/mean(tot_biomass),
  sd=sd(tot_biomass),
  avg_w_sumslopes=mean(sum_w_slopes,na.rm = T),
  mean_slope=mean(mean_slopes)
)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'composition', 'nutrients', 'temperature'.
## You can override using the `.groups` argument.
complete_aggr<-full_join(new_selection_mean,complete_aggr,by=join_by(composition,nutrients,temperature))%>%
  mutate(richness=as.factor(richness))

complete_aggr<-complete_aggr%>%mutate(abs_sum_slope=abs(sum_slopes))

async_aggr <- async_aggr %>% 
  mutate(RD_group = cut(avg_w_sumslopes, breaks = quantile(async_aggr$avg_w_sumslopes),include.lowest=T,labels=c("low","medium low","medium high","high")))

plot_int_sync_RD<-ggplot(data=async_aggr,aes(y=1/CV,x=synchrony_Gross,color=RD_group))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method="lm")

stat. averaging ?

stat_av_df<-complete_ts%>%group_by(sample_ID,temperature,nutrients,richness,predict_spec)%>%summarize(mean_biomass=mean(biomass),
                                                                                                      var_biomass=var(biomass))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'sample_ID', 'temperature', 'nutrients',
## 'richness'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
stat_avg<-ggplot(data=stat_av_df,aes(x=log10(mean_biomass),y=log10(var_biomass)))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method="lm")+
  facet_wrap(~richness)

stat_av_df<-stat_av_df%>%dplyr::filter(mean_biomass!=0)

m_stat_avg<-lm(data=stat_av_df,log10(var_biomass)~log10(mean_biomass)*richness)

summary(m_stat_avg)
